content.detailedDescription:
These 2 videos were taken at my mom's house while we were chatting in the backyard, during our christmas dinner. the first one was around 01:10am on december 25th, 2015. by the way, my mom lives in itaipuaçu - which is a small distric of the city of marica, located in the state of rio de janeiro, brazil.

it is important to mention that we first saw this phenomenon on december 25th, 2015. then, again on decebember 27th, 2015. however, the first sightseeing (dec 25th) was only a white blinking light. video is attached.
that's what really caught our attention - looking at this white blinking light in the sky. it kind of looks like the morse code - i am not sure though.

two days after the first contact with this phenomenon, and out of the blue and around the same time (12:40am), this red and green light started to fall from the white light. 

at first (first video and continuing on the second video), we thought it was a ballon, but since the phenomenon was strange to our previous knowledge of flying objects (like airplanes, helicopters, drones, etc) we started to wonder why this bright white light was blinking like that. besides, you will be able to see on the second video how other lights are "ejected" from the white one.

i need to mention that i am into spirituality and truly believe in other forms of life outside of our planet. with that said, my reaction was based on joy and surprise - since i had never seen anything like this in my whole life. my family members were actually joking about the phenomenon, but some (who were skeptical at first) started to wonder what was that unidentified flying object. 

the video made on december 25th had the object descending before we lost sight. the video on december 27th had the object disappearing in the sky (as seen on the video).  

last but not least, this strange object appeared on the sky practically in the same location - it was located in the same place at 333 degrees (nw).

there are a lot of videos on youtube showing ufo's around here (in itaipuaçu, rio de janeiro, brazil). it's important to say that this is an area of low density population, surrounded by forests, mountains and the ocean.

any other question, please don't hesitate to contact me. 

please, reply with some feedback.

thank you!

lessandro encarnacao
whatsapp: +55 22 99930-9129
content.summary: A weird blinking white, red and green lights never seen before in my life.

content.detailedDescription:
October 4th, 2015

my fiance and i spent the day in whiteshell provincial park, pine point trail to be exact, getting our engagement photos taken. we were there for the majority of the day and left when it began to get dark, roughly 7 - 730pm. our return path to winnipeg took us down highway 15. as we came down 15 heading west into the city, shortly after passing the perimeter i glance ahead as you always do when driving and i see a pulsating red light in the sky. i thought absolutely nothing of it as it looked exactly like the pulsating red light you would see on the top of a cell phone tower which is also relevant because the height of the light was also matching that of a cell phone tower. we continued our drive down 15 (now dugald rd) and it was maybe a minute or two later i happen to glance over to my right (compass north), it dawned on me this should be the general area where that pulsating light should be, only i didn't see any such tower. i glanced up through the windsheild and what i seen made me slam on the breaks in the middle of the road. it was an equilateral triangle shaped craft, all black except for the pulsing red in the core and blueish-green lights on the tips of the craft. there was one or two cars behind me that swerved around me, surprisingly not honking their horns. i pulled over to the shoulder immediately and got out of the car. i stood there looking up at this craft as it hovered in a stationary position for a few seconds before it very slowly started to move down dugald rd in the direction we just came from (east). i watched on, and so did my fiance from the car, as it slowly made a greater distance between us. after a few more seconds of watching it i jumped back in the car and sped up to the nearest intersection to u-turn and chase this craft as long as we could. by this point it was an incredible distance away so we pulled over and watched as the pulsating red light ascended higher and higher until we could see it no more.

oddly enough the next day we found out that the building we seen the craft hovering above is named 'superior technologies'. this is not my attempt at some cheap humour, it is simply the truth. if anything, i feel this would be some humour on the occupants part. i have enclosed an image of the building it was above. thank you.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Returning from our engagement photo shoot, we see a ufo in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I had just woke up at 5:ooam december 27 2015 in santa cruz california. i sat on my bed and gazed out the window (facing north/west)and noticed what i thought was an airplane. the lights appeared a little bit more intense than a normal plane so i got up and walked to the window to get a closer view. when i got to the window i noticed that the object appeared to just be hovering with slight flutters in movement. the lights on the bottom had no unique intensity in color but they were constantly flashing and appeared to have some pattern or sequence to them...I'm not very good at judging distance, but it appeared as if it was 2 or more miles away and lower than a commercial jet would fly but similar to the height that a jet would fly. it was hard to get a good solid look at any detail because of the distance...I watched it hover and do its light show for about 10 minutes and then i had to leave the room to get ready for work. when i came back to the room 40 minutes later it was gone...I did not take a picture because the distance of the object would of provided no details that would of been helpful.

content.detailedDescription: Driving to work between 7:30 and 8:00 on the saturday after thanksgiving 2014. i noticed a black object in the sky over the road in front of me. at first glance, i thought it was a hot air balloon but then i new it wasn't because it was 18 degrees, much to cold for that. as i got closer to the object, it looked more like the thing the astronauts used to land back on earth after going to the moon or the machines the people of india have ancient pictures of. it didn't seem to be moving. it's color was the darkest black you could imagine. the sky was clear with no clouds and no planes in sight. as i was coming up to exit 27, i stopped on the ramp. the car in front of me stopped also. the object started moving north west and it seemed to be creating heat waves around it and seemed to be even darker black now.I decided to drive up the hill in front of me to get a better view of the object. it took me 15 seconds or so to get thru the parking lot and go behind the buildings. when i stopped, i got out of my truck. the object was gone. from my vantage point i could see for miles in the direction the object was moving but there was no sign of the object. the total time that elapsed from the first sight to loosing sight of the object was around 5 minutes.
content.summary: Observed black object stationary in clear blue sky over i-70 . moved west slowly.Seemed to create heat waves around it. then vanished.

content.detailedDescription: Lincoln park, mi.  richmond street between dix and fort st.  it was in the afternoon sometime when i had walked out to my car parked on the street in front of the house.  i heard what i thought was a jet flying low coming from the east.  air traffic is not unusual as i lived near detroit metropolitan airport. this noise got very loud very quickly and seemed to be heading right for me.  it also seemed like it was following the exact street path. i was both frightened and intrigued.  i was scared something might fall out of the sky on me, but had no time to react and run or hide. as the noise peaked overhead, it was almost unbearably loud and sounded like an engine of some sort, rumbling. i covered my ears. i felt the vibration.  it blew the treetops as it passed and i could not believe that i didn't see anything. it continued west away from the detroit river, but the sound faded in volume and duration much more quickly than when it built up and approached, almost sounding like it was ascending rapidly. i stood, bewildered and searched the sky for something, anything, that would explain the sound. i then looked at the house and noticed my roommate in the open window. we both were quiet for a moment, looking at each other in amazement. finally, i asked him if he "saw" that, he said yes, and then i corrected myself and asked if he heard it. he confirmed. he said he did not actually see anything either.  i looked up and down the street for anyone else who may have experienced what we did. i saw no one, (which i thought was weird because this was a really, really, loud noise)and things seemed normal. i shook it off explaining it away to myself as an airplane, and got in my car and went about my day. there were no reports on the news to my knowledge of any airplanes having difficulty at metro airport that day.  it felt like something different.  it has always bothered me.  the sound alone made me think this should have been something huge i could see. it almost seemed like whatever was there was invisible or cloaked.  the trees moving with the noise made me think so.
content.summary: I was on street by my car. i heard loud noise i thought was low flying jet approaching very quickly. i got extremely loud as it passed over head, had to cover ears. i saw nothing and could not believe it. roomate heard it at house, saw nothing.

content.detailedDescription:
Returning to missouri from godfrey il, ,driving south on hwy 270 on a stretch of the highway that airplanes fly over before landing at st. louis lambert field.  it was approx 6:30pm cst, clear sky, twilight-blue color sky.                                                                            i have seen planes in this area before when they are approaching lambert field to land.  this occurance i saw many bright white lights to my right and looked to watch the plane fly over the highway.  i saw approx 5 bright white lights that i assumed were the lights the planes use when landing.  i realize that i did not see an airplane shape,nor did i see any other color lights that planes usually have. i just saw a group of bright lights. as we traveled south on the highway, i followed the lights to watch the airplane descending.
  
as i was watching, the lights/plane(?), in the blink of an eye i saw what became only 3 bright white, round lights that formed a triangle shape, like an elongated triagle, 2 lights closer and one like at the point.  i could see blue sky all around, no solid triangular shape, just the lights. it was pointed a little more north than it had been. i did a doubletake because this surprised me so much.  later, while thinking about what i saw, i realized that there had been no sound!  landing planes make a loud noise you can hear when they are flying here.  


a few years ago, there was a sighting of a black triangular ufo in the alton il/st. louis mo areas. this had even been on national news.  there was no solid shape to see, but the lights i saw formed into the same type triangular shape.  


as i saw this, i thought whaaaaaaat am i seeing? i watched the lights as we drove further down the highway until it was out of my sight.  all of this probably only took 2 or 3 minutes.  


i still wonder what i saw.  i honestly don't think it was a plane.    i saw 3 bright white round lights in a triangular shape.  there was nothing in the news here if anyone elsesaw it.  (my husband was driving the car but didn't see this.)
content.summary: Airplane lights turned into a triangular shape of 3  bright, round lights.

electric trail. the pacific electric trail is a hiking/running/biking trail that runs through rancho cucamonga. i headed east. i could still hear the helicopter and when i could fully see cucamonga peak and the surrounding foothills i looked in the direction of the helicopter sound. i figured it had to be searching for something since it was already going on being around the area over an hour. i saw a blinking red light which was attached to the chopper but the chopper had no other lights including search illuminated. it was going back and forth in multiple directions. i then realized that it had to be chasing something. i figured an off roader running from police. i didnt see anything on the surface but noticed a light in front of the helicopter that seemed to be going in between the trees on the foothill east of the peak. i was dumbfounded. at first i thought motorcycle but the light was moving too fast. then it seemed to clear the trees and i could see a dense ball of light heading east across the front of the foothill. i could see the red beacon light of the chopper and saw and heard it following the object. the object went from east to west then over the hill all while the chopper followed. it skimmed the top of the hill and went west and shot straight up the face of the peak and kept raising. thats when i saw the movement of another dense ball of light. the chopper then went straight up after the ball of light. the ball of light then came back around and leveled out and both it and the helicopter went east towards san bernardino where i lost visual. i didnt see that incident lasted from 7:58pm to 8:25pm on 11/3/15

content.detailedDescription:
I was photographing old mines and fall foliage between leadville and mt. democrat on a clear afternoon (9-12-15).

the object appeared in one in a short series of photos taken at the site of an abandoned mine dump and mill.  it was between 5 and 10 mile from me and from the perspective of the photo, i would estimate its length at several football fields.

the object may have been cloaked to the human eye.  it the actual image it is barely visible.  the camera was a nikon d7200, the newest model in the series, which, because it eliminates the high-pass filter, may pick up more of the infra-red spectrum.  looking at the photo, and object, it almost appears cloaked.  

when the object is subjected to the photoshop "emboss" filter, its shape is readily apparent as a cylinder or cigar with four uniform rounded appendages...Two near each end.

the embossed image gives strong detail in terms of shape and configuration.

i didn't "feel" anything at the time, although, with other sightings i have had, i felt calm and reassured by their presence...Never threatened.

there are photos taken within 15-20 seconds of this photo which show nothing in the area.

the original photo is a raw (nef) image 20.5 x 13" @ 300dpi.  enclosed is a far smaller jpeg
content.summary: Appeared in one frame of photo series when processing in photoshop.

content.detailedDescription:
I live in the fourth ward of uptown, charlotte north carolina. i knew that there would be a full moon on dec 25 2015, it would be the first full moon on christmas since 1977 and i wanted to see if i could locate that moon as it was dusk, and i had my cell phone in my hand because i wanted to take a picture of the full moon, so i went out on my patio (i live on the ground floor) and started looking up at the cloudy sky towards uptown charlotte's skyline (trade and tryon streets) and i couldn't find the moon but instead i saw 2 orange orbs at 5:53pm and it was perplexing to me, i had never seen anything like it ... so i kept looking at the 2 orange orbs, and then there were 3! and the 3rd one which was at a lower altitude shot up quickly and joined closer to the other 2 and the 3 were in a triangle formation or in a crooked line they moved away from uptown skyline towards my direction! the 3 orange circular orbs were round and a very bright orange with white lights, they were 100% silent and there were no other aircraft in the sky/area. they just moved silently like they were gliding overhead. i almost thought they were maybe experimental large high tech drones? but they didn't have feet like drones and were way the heck too high up in the clouds to be regular drones.
i ran upstairs one level to get a better view of the open cloudy sky and started taking pictures with my iphone 4s of these 3 silent bright orange orbs, they are date and time stamped and i used no flash, times taken are within 2 minutes between 5:53pm and 5:55pm. the best picture i captured of the orange orbs is photo #5 where you can clearly see they are bright orange orbs, if you zoom in you will notice all 3 have 2 darker orange lights in the identical spot identically spaced apart on them on the front of the orb.
as the large orbs were almost overhead a friend, was coming over, because we were going to order in chinese food. i saw him down beneath me and said "hey, look up in the sky, check out those 3 orange things!" "what could they be???" he says "helicopters?" i said "no way, they are not helicopters they are 100% silent you can hear helicopters and they are too close together and helos are not orange" so i looked down at him for a second and told him to just go into my apt and wait for me, and as i did that i looked back up and all 3 were gone. had he not come at that time and thrown my focus maybe i could have seen how they just disappeared into the clouds or how they disappeared...(that bummed me out that he distracted me) sigh... then i went inside and kept coming out periodically and looked into the sky as i waited for my dinner to be delivered and i didn't see the orbs again...However i did finally find the full moon in the sky.
content.summary: Went out on patio to see the full moon at dusk instead saw 2 then 3 orange bright orbs moving super fast

content.detailedDescription:
I was traveling as passenger with my wife by car to a christmas celebration. it was dark out. heading east on cold spring road in milwaukee, wi at about 68th street i noticed , to the s/w, one orange light. i thought it might be a plane. it appeared to in the atmosphere at about 5000 to 10000 feet. within seconds i saw a second light about 5 degrees lower and to the left.  they appeared about plane or helicopter size at that distance. the color was predominately orange with small flashes/pulses of red and white. they moved between 30 and 40 degrees in the sky.

i watched these for about three minutes.  they stayed in the same general area, did not fly in formation.  they move independent of each other, never got really close to each other but were obviously together. they moved sparingly and hovered about 40% of the time.  i watched as we  drove, at times losing sight do to tree/building obstruction, but did re-establish visual. they did not "blink out" but were just gone after i came out from behind an obstruction. the total time was about 3 minutes.

they seemed to far away to be drones.  maybe helicopters in the distance, however the color was something i've never seen in the sky before outside of the 4th of july.  they were to far away and vague for me to say "yes, these are ufo's", however that would be my best guess.  i was excited during and after the event.

my wife did not see the objects. she was driving and we were eastbound.  the lights were s/w. my thoughts on reporting is that it's not a strong case, however it may confirm others in the area.

what made this interesting is that on christmas late evening in 1982, my wife and i had an experience (unreported) where our cars lights and radio went out.  it just lost power on the way home from relatives in the late evening. it was on a deserted interstate close enough to a wayside to roll in. we slept there the entire night and have very little recollection of it. we actually joke about maybe being abducted but have no effects of he incident. the car was fine in the morning.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two orangish lights maneuvering in the s/w sky.

content.detailedDescription:
While driving in a southwest-ish direction on peralta ave oakland ca usa 94607, 1pm clear blue sky, i observed the brightest white daytime starlike luminescence ive ever seen, directly in front of me in the direction of travel, about 30 to 40 degrees above the horizon.

the appearance seemed to hover, stationary, emitting extremely bright light like a star, just apparently sitting there shining or reflecting light as if a polished mirror with no apparent motion, hard to not notice.

seemed to hover for about 20-30 seconds, the brightest thing ive ever seen in the sky other than the sun. i watch a lot of aircraft traffic and it was brighter than any aircraft i have ever seen.

after seemingly motionless initially it zipped away into the distance directly away from my vantage point, either that or it shrunk away to nothing. it just rapidly disappeared by shrinking or shooting away very very rapidly.
content.summary: Extremely bright white daytime blue sky hovering  starlike appearance

content.detailedDescription:
For many months now, every evening just after dark while walking my dog at the edge of the lake, i see what appears as extremely bright white stars that color change to green and red.They are low in the sky, sometimes lower than planes and helicopters but still look like a bright star changing colors. if i shine my flashlight at them they immediately start to sway back and forth while slowly moving in my direction. they are always out over the lake or very near the lake. some nights there seems to be alot of activity and others not as much, however i see them every night unless the clouds are out. once in awhile there has been a much larger light, but only one.
one night they moved so close that i became afraid and left the area.
content.summary: Extremely bright starlike, over clearlake,seen for months every night

content.detailedDescription:
I was standing outside in north oakland, looked up at the sky toward the west, over the city of san francisco (though the city is not visible from this vantage point) and saw two stars about as far apart as either side of orion's belt, perhaps slightly further apart. the lights were horizontally arranged, on the same plane, and white. the two lights maintained a perfectly even distance from one another during the entire course of the event.

i observed both lights move in tandem, slowly to the south. the movement was steady, and scaled upon a backdrop which appears two or so miles away, they moved at least a half-mile. as a distant object, the actual object's movement would have been a much greater distance in that interval of time. i can only give comparison given my surroundings. the lights ascended, in perfect formation after moving to the south, and ascended slightly, a few degrees of arc. the lights faded from white to a fainter blue hue over this short period of time, as if they were moving up and out, and the formation was no longer visible. the lights indicated either a solid object, or two objects locked in complete tandem. it would have been an enormous object, and could have been out over the ocean beyond san francisco, or in the upper atmosphere. once again, the lights were as far apart as either side of orion's belt, perhaps even further apart. there was no blinking or typical atmospheric distortion. it looked like two stars light years apart at even magnitude simply moved across the sky together horizontally, and then moved diagonally and away until they were unable to be seen. the disappearance was gradual, but very quick. the formation caught my eye immediately. i was looking at the stars, as i often do, and two stars in a horizontal bar formation moving across the sky is definitely out of the ordinary. both lights ascended and disappeared from view at the same time.

planes from the oakland airport and san francisco airport are seen at regular intervals, and an occasional drone and helicopter. not only was this further up in the sky, but further away, and the light pattern of planes is utterly different. i am also able to make out the body of a plane, even in the night. i've already seen numerous typical airliners since the event. the object was miles away, and the further away the lights were from me, the further apart they would have been, so i am not able to estimate a size, if it was even a single object. my speculation is that the span of the object, if solid, would have cast a shadow over downtown san francisco.

it would have been impossible to film or picture, but the event would have perplexed anyone. i've never seen anything like it. no substances were involved in this sighting.
content.summary: Over sf bay/ocean, star-like lights move in tandem, fade, and ascend into nothingness
